description: A concentric ditched enclosure surrounding a vertical sided pit. The site appears to have been active around the 1st CE and has been interpreted as a shrine or ceremonial enclosure.
bibliography: Cornwall Council Historic Environment Service. “An Archaeological Evaluation Report on Phase 3 Enabling Development Works, Tremough, Penryn, Cornwall.” Archaeology Data Service, 2008. http://archaeologydataservice.ac.uk/archives/view/greylit/details.cfm?id=25901.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Tremough, Penryn (Site 3) (Cornwall).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
